{{for|the Soviet and Russian scientist|Alexey Aleksandrovich Alexandrov}} {{use dmy dates|date=October 2016}} [[File:Александров Алексей Иванович.jpg|thumb]] '''Aleksey Ivanovich Aleksandrov''' ({{lang-ru|Алексе́й Ива́нович Алекса́ндров}}, born 3 May 1952<ref name="Duma">Official website of the [[State Duma]] of the Russian Federation. [https://web.archive.org/web/20071109150935/http://www.duma.gov.ru/index.jsp?t=history/3/99100010.html Aleksey Ivanovich Aleksandrov] {{ru icon}}</ref> in [[Saint Petersburg|Leningrad]], [[Soviet Union]]) is a [[Russians|Russian]] lawyer, businessman, and politician.
In 1993–2003 he was a deputy of the [[State Duma]] first from [[Our Home – Russia]] then from [[Unity (Russian political party)|Unity]] and then [[United Russia]]. Since 2004, he has been the representative of the legislative assembly of [[Kaluga Oblast]] in the [[Federation Council of Russia]].<ref name="FC">Official website of the [[Federation Council of Russia]]. [http://www.council.gov.ru/staff/members/functionary1630332.html Aleksey Ivanovich Aleksandrov] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100712011440/http://www.council.gov.ru/staff/members/functionary1630332.html |date=12 July 2010 }} {{ru icon}}</ref>
