[[File:Bhic.gif|right]] The '''British Horse Industry Confederation''' is a representative umbrella organisation for both professional and amateur involvement in [[equestrianism|equestrian]] activities in [[Great Britain]]. The organisation is formed of the [[British Equestrian Federation]], the [[Thoroughbred Breeders Association]] and the [[British Horseracing Authority]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=British Equestrian Federation|url=http://www.bef.co.uk/About_the_BEF|title=About the BEF|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100401165124/http://www.bef.co.uk/About_the_BEF|archivedate=2010-04-01|df=}}</ref> It also has representation from the [[British Horse Society]] and [[British Equestrian Trade Association]] (both members of the BEF) and from the [[British Equine Veterinary Association]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=British Horse Industry Confederation|title=About Us|url=http://www.bhic.co.uk/about.html|access-date=2013-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502170304/http://www.bhic.co.uk/about.html#|archive-date=2012-05-02|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
==Activities== The organisation represents the interests of the equestrian industry in dealings and reports with government.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs|date=March 2004|url=http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/horses/documents/bhic-leaflet.pdf|title=Joint research on the Horse Industry in Great Britain|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110113110204/http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/horses/documents/bhic-leaflet.pdf|archivedate=2011-01-13|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=UK Parliament|title=Bound Volume Hansard - Debate|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200001/cmhansrd/vo010430/debtext/10430-17.htm}}</ref>
In 2005, the BHIC published the first national strategy for the horse industry in England and Wales, in partnership with the government departments from Defra and the Department for Culture, Media and Sport.<ref>{{cite news|publisher=Horse and Hound|last=Tyzack|first=Anna|title=New strategy for the equine industry|url=http://www.horseandhound.co.uk/news/397/71735.html|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610080911/http://www.horseandhound.co.uk/news/397/71735.html|archivedate=2011-06-10|df=}}</ref>
