{{Spanish name|Kosturakis|Yanarakis}}

'''Nicolás Kosturakis Yanarakis''' ({{lang-el|Νικόλας Κωστουράκης Γιανναράκης}}) (April 4, 1912 – November 17, 1986) son of Antonios Kostourakis Troullinos and Eleny Giannarakis Kanou, was born in the village of [[Kalyves]], in the municipality of [[Apokoronas]], in the island of [[Crete]], Greece.

He was a notable [[Greeks|Greek]] businessman and philanthropist who emigrated to [[Mexico]] in 1930. As a person of great political and social influence in both [[Greece]] and Mexico, he was also known for his notorious charitable support, and was awarded the diplomatic title of [[Consul (representative)|Honorary Consul]] of Greece in the Mexican city of Chihuahua. He was a [[Freemasonry|Freemason]] of the Grand Lodge of the State of Chihuahua, "Cosmos".

Along with his wife for more than 30 years, María Lucila García Stevens, he fathered three sons and two daughters: Nicolás Kosturakis García, Demetrio Kosturakis Garcia, Jorge Kosturakis García, María Lucila Kosturakis García, and Eleny Kosturakis García.

