'''Walter Faria''' (born 1955) is a Brazilian businessman, the owner of [[Grupo Petrópolis]], the brewer of Brazil's second-largest selling beer.
==Early life== Walter Faria was born in 1955.<ref name=Forbes/>
==Career== According to Forbes, Faria has an estimated net worth of $3.8 billion in January 2015.<ref name=Forbes/>
==Personal life== He is married with one child.<ref name=Forbes/>
